feat(api): :sparkles: add per-IP rate limiting middleware

Why:
The API has no protection against abuse. A single client can
make unlimited requests, potentially causing service degradation
for all users and exhausting server resources.

What:
Implement sliding window rate limiter backed by Redis. Default
config allows 100 requests per 15-minute window with configurable
parameters. Returns 429 with Retry-After header when limit exceeded.

Ticket: PROJ-312
Signed-off-by: Alice Developer <alice@example.com>
